#: ../../recording.rst:2
msgid "Recording"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:5
msgid "Steps to Follow from the Home Screen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:7
msgid ""
"**Note**: This procedure enables you to record only the project that is "
"named in the blue recording area. If a different project is shown, or no "
"project is shown, you need to record from the Project Management screen "
"as explained `below <https://btt-"
"recorder.readthedocs.io/en/latest/recording.html#steps-to-follow-from-"
"project-management>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:9
msgid "On the home screen, tap in the blue recording area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:11
msgid ""
"If the Security warning shows, tap in the box before the words ‘Do not "
"remind again.’ so that there is a checkmark in the box. Then tap the word"
" ‘ALLOW.’ (This is the only time you will need to check and allow.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:13 ../../recording.rst:51
msgid "Check the information on the top gray bar:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:15 ../../recording.rst:53
msgid "Target Language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:16 ../../recording.rst:54
msgid "Project Type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:17 ../../recording.rst:55
msgid "Book"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:18 ../../recording.rst:56
msgid "Chapter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:19 ../../recording.rst:57
msgid "Verse or Chunk"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:21 ../../recording.rst:59
msgid "Use the + and – signs to correct the chapter or verse/chunk number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:23 ../../recording.rst:61
msgid ""
"Tap the Microphone icon. (See more `detailed instructions <https://btt-"
"recorder.readthedocs.io/en/latest/recording.html#detailed-instructions-"
"for-the-recording-window>`_ for recording below.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:25 ../../recording.rst:63
msgid "Record the verse or chunk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:27
msgid ""
"Tap the Pause icon (2 vertical lines) when done saying the verse/chunk "
"(the Pause icon replaces the Play icon)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:29 ../../recording.rst:67
msgid "Tap the Checkmark icon in the bottom blue bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:31 ../../recording.rst:69
msgid ""
"Edit and rate the recording. See `Rate the Target Language Recording "
"<https://btt-recorder.readthedocs.io/en/latest/editing3.html#rate-the-"
"target-language-recording>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:33
msgid "Save the recording. The recording window closes and the home screen shows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:35
msgid ""
"Repeat steps 1 to 9 for all verses in the book. Be sure to change the "
"chapter and/or verse number (step 3) each time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:39
msgid "Steps to Follow from the Project Management Screen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:41
msgid "On the home screen, tap in the green Project Management side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:43
msgid "Tap on the project bar that displays the language and book."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:45
msgid "Tap on the chapter bar that needs to be recorded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:47
msgid "On the verse bar that needs to be recorded, tap on the Microphone icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:49
msgid ""
"**HINT**: This is an easy way to keep track of which verses/chunks have "
"recordings already so that you don’t unnecessarily record the same item "
"over and over. It is also an easy way to navigate to the specific item "
"you want to record."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:65
msgid "Tap the Pause icon when done saying the verse/chunk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:71
msgid ""
"Save the recording. The recording window closes and the Project "
"Management window for the verses in that chapter appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:73
msgid ""
"On the next verse bar that needs to be recorded, tap on the Microphone "
"icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:75
msgid "Repeat steps 5 to 13 for all verses in the book."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:80
msgid "Detailed instructions for the Recording Window"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:82
msgid ""
"In the Recording window you can see the Target Language, the Source, the "
"Book, the Chapter and the Verse in the gray bar at the top of the screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:84
msgid ""
"If source audio is available, tap the Play button in the gray bar at the "
"bottom of the screen to listen to the source language for that particular"
" verse/chunk. The green dot will move along the line. The numbers on the "
"left of the line count down and the numbers on the right count up the "
"length of the audio recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:86
msgid "Listen to the verse or chunk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:88
msgid "The green dot will move along the line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:90
msgid "The numbers on the left of the line count up as the recording plays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:92
msgid "The numbers on the right display the length of the audio recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:94
msgid "Tap the Microphone icon in the blue bar to start recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:96
msgid "Speak clearly and loudly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:98
msgid ""
"It is recommended that you use a separate microphone or a headset with a "
"microphone, not just the microphone that is built into the tablet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:100
msgid ""
"As you begin to speak you will see a wavy line appear on the screen which"
" is a result of the sound of your voice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:102
msgid "When done with that verse or chunk, tap the Pause button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:104
msgid "You can also tap Pause to temporarily Pause recording."
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:106
msgid "You can then start recording again by tapping on the Microphone icon"
msgstr ""

#: ../../recording.rst:108
msgid "6 When you are finished, tap the Checkmark to go to the Edit window."
msgstr ""

